%% Diagram: ReadIndex vs lease-based linearizable read in etcd
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant L as Leader
    participant F1 as Follower 1
    participant F2 as Follower 2

    Note over C,F2: Mode 1 - ReadIndex (default, safe)
    C->>L: linearizable get(k)
    L->>L: capture commitIndex i
    par Heartbeat round
        L->>F1: heartbeat
        L->>F2: heartbeat
    end
    F1-->>L: heartbeat ack
    F2-->>L: heartbeat ack
    Note over L: Quorum confirmed leadership at i
    L->>L: wait until applied >= i
    L-->>C: value at i

    Note over C,F2: Mode 2 - Lease-based read (faster, assumes bounded clock drift)
    C->>L: linearizable get(k)
    Note over L: Lease still valid in local clock?
    alt Lease valid
        L->>L: serve from local state
        L-->>C: value
    else Lease expired
        L->>L: fall back to ReadIndex
    end
